# Backend Agent Rules

## Gemini Live Session Lifecycle

The async context manager from `gemini_client.aio.live.connect()` MUST be stored as `self._session_context` on the Room instance. A local variable will be garbage-collected, killing the WebSocket.

```python
# CORRECT
self._session_context = gemini_client.aio.live.connect(model=MODEL, config=config)
self.gemini_session = await self._session_context.__aenter__()

# WRONG — session dies immediately
ctx = gemini_client.aio.live.connect(model=MODEL, config=config)
self.gemini_session = await ctx.__aenter__()
```

## Caption Routing

Always send TWO caption messages per transcript:
1. `side: "theirs"` → listener (translated text)
2. `side: "mine"` → speaker (their own words echoed back)

## Error Isolation

Vision, narration, and sentiment are non-critical. Always wrap in `asyncio.create_task()` + try/except. Never let API failures crash the WebSocket connection.

## Cost Tracking

Every new API call path MUST include `log_api_call(name, cost, context)`. Audio input logging batches to every ~30s (960K bytes), not per chunk.

## Vision Gating

Only broadcast `visual_caption` when scene labels differ >50% from the previous detection AND 12+ seconds have elapsed. Store label sets in `self._last_vision_labels`.

## Concurrency

- Vision API is synchronous gRPC — ALWAYS wrap in `asyncio.to_thread()` + `_vision_sem`
- Gemini narration calls go through `_gemini_sem` — never call without it
- State mutations (screenshots, captions, etc.) use `async with self._state_lock:`
- Audio `send_audio_to_gemini()` is the critical path — no semaphore, no lock
